ts_awards.shtml | date = December 2007 | accessdate = 17 March 2013 | title = Bardwell football founder named unsung hero | publisher = [[BBC Sport]] }}</ref> |- |align=center|2008 |{{flag|ENG}} !scope=row|{{sort|Geyser, Ben|Ben Geyser}} |{{sort|Dorset, Dorchester|[[Dorchester, Dorset|Dorchester]], Dorset}} |[[BBC South]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dorsetecho.co.uk/sport/3945303.BBC_nomination_is_a____fitting_tribute____for_Geyser/|title=BBC nomination is a 'fitting tribute' for Geyser|date=3 December 2008|work=[[Dorset Echo]]|publisher=[[Newsquest]]|accessdate=15 January 2009}}</ref> |[[Boxing]] |for setting up three boxing clubs, and campaigning for a permanent home for the [[Dorchester, Dorset|Dorchester]] Amateur Boxing Club.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/tv_and_radio/sports_personality_of_the_year/7777915.stm|title=Boxing club hero wins Unsung 2008 |date=14 December 2008|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=23 January 2009| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081218080303/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/tv_and_radio/sports_personality_of_the_year/7777915.stm| archivedate=18 December 2008| deadurl= no}}</ref> |align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dorsetecho.co.uk/sport/3980245.Geyser___s_accolade_can_inspire_next_generation/|title=Geyser's accolade can inspire next generation|date=16 December 2008|work=[[Dorset Echo]]|publisher=[[Newsquest]]|accessdate=12 January 2009}}</ref> |- |align=center|2009 |{{flag|ENG}} !scope=row|{{sort|Adcock, Doreen|Doreen Adcock}} |{{sort|Buckinghamshire, Milton Keynes|[[Milton Keynes]], Buckinghamshire}} |[[BBC East]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/lookeast/content/articles/2009/11/26/sports_personality_2009_feature.shtml|title=Edwards is East Sports Personality 2009|publisher=[[BBC East]]|accessdate=14 December 2009| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20091213173255/http://www.bbc.co.uk/lookeast/content/articles/2009/11/26/sports_personality_2009_feature.shtml| archivedate= 13 Decem