{{use dmy dates|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox sportsperson | name = Calvin Greenaway | birth_name = | image = | caption = | nationality = Antigua and Barbuda | sport = Sprinting | event = 4 × 100 metres relay | club = | collegeteam = | birth_date = {{birth date|1948|5|11|df=yes}} | birth_place = | death_date = {{death date and age|2016|1|14|1948|5|11|df=yes}}<ref name="Obituary">{{cite news|last = Baptiste|first = Neto|title = Athletics Fraternity Mourns Greenaway's Passing|newspaper = The Daily Observer|location = Antigua|date = 16 January 2016|url = https://antiguaobserver.com/athletics-fraternity-mourns-greenaways-passing/|access-date = 30 January 2018}}</ref> | death_place = | height = | weight = }}
'''Calvin Greenaway''' (11 May 1948 &ndash; 14 January 2016) was an Antigua and Barbuda [[sprint (running)|sprinter]]. He competed in the [[Athletics at the 1976 Summer Olympics – Men's 4 × 100 metres relay|men's 4 × 100 metres relay]] at the [[1976 Summer Olympics]].<ref name="SportsRef">{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/gr/calvin-greenaway-1.html |title=Calvin Greenaway Olympic Results |accessdate=19 August 2017}}</ref>
