{{distinguish|Champions (2018 film)}} {{Infobox film | name = Champion | image = Champion poster.jpg | caption = Promotional poster | film name = {{Film name | hangul = 챔피언 | hanja = | rr = Chaempieon | mr = }} | director = Kim Yong-wan | producer = Han Dong-hwan | writer = Kim Yong-wan | screenplay = | based on = | starring = {{ubl|[[Ma Dong-seok]]|[[Kwon Yul (actor)|Kwon Yul]]|[[Han Ye-ri]]}} | music = | cinematography = Yoo Ji-sun | editing = | studio = | distributor = [[Warner Bros.]] | released = {{film date|2018|5|1|South Korea}} | runtime = 108 minutes | country = South Korea | language = Korean | budget = | gross = {{USD|8.7 million}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Champion (2018)|url=http://koreanfilm.or.kr/eng/films/index/filmsView.jsp?movieCd=20189783|website=Korean Film Biz Zone}}</ref> }}
'''''Champion''''' is a 2018 South Korean [[Sports film|sports]] [[comedy film]] directed by Kim Yong-wan. The film stars [[Ma Dong-seok]], [[Kwon Yul (actor)|Kwon Yul]], and [[Han Ye-ri]]. It is related to arm wrestling competition. The movie is rated 9.4/10 in Asian TV Website within the first month of release.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hancinema.net/kwon-yul-and-han-ye-ri-to-star-in-champion-109729.html|title=Kwon Yul and Han Ye-ri to star in "Champion"|date=4 June 2017|work=Joy News|publisher=Hancinema|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Yoon|first1=Min-sik|title=‘Mavely’ shadows hero Sylvester Stallone in arm wrestling film ‘Champion’|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20180402000812|accessdate=May 22, 2018|work=Korea Herald|date=April 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>Champion (2018) Movie, Asiantv Website, available at http://myasiantv.se/movie/champion/?utm_source=featured&utm_medium=home&utm_campaign=tracking</ref>
==Plot== The film tells the story of the adopted Mark who was a former arm wrestler but now works as a bouncer. He goes to South Korea for a competition to search for his mother who gave him up for adoption as a child. With help of his friend, Jin-ki, Mark finds his real family, only to learn that his mother had died. He then meets his step-sister and her family whom he never knew. Through his mother's emails that he came to read he came to know what it meant to feel her pain of abandoning him. He later wins the national tournament against his opponents and in the end, defeats the opponent named Punch in the final.<ref>Champion (2018) Movie, Asiantv Website, available at http://myasiantv.se/movie/champion/?utm_source=featured&utm_medium=home&utm_campaign=tracking</ref>
