{{Infobox building | name = Charles W. Stockey Centre for the Performing Arts | native_name = | native_name_lang = | former_names = | alternate_names = | status = Finished | image = | image_alt = | caption = | map_type = Canada Ontario | map_alt = | map_caption = Location in Ontario | altitude = {{convert|176|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | building_type = | architectural_style = | structural_system = | cost = CAD$12.4 million | ren_cost = | client = | owner = | current_tenants = [[Festival of the Sound]] | landlord = | location = [[Parry Sound, Ontario|Parry Sound]], [[Ontario]], Canada | address = 2 Bay Street, Parry Sound, ON P2A&nbsp;1S3 | location_town = | location_country = | coordinates = {{coord|45|20|21|N|80|02|21|W|region:CA-ON|display=inline,title}} | groundbreaking_date = | start_date = Spring 2002 | completion_date = | completed_date = | opened_date = | inauguration_date = July 2003 | renovation_date = | demolition_date = | destruction_date = | height = | diameter = | antenna_spire = | roof = | top_floor = | other_dimensions = | floor_count = 3 | floor_area = {{convert|2500|m2|sqft|-2|abbr=on}} | seating_type = | seating_capacity = 480 | elevator_count = 1 | main_contractor = ElisDon Limited | architect = | architecture_firm = Keith Loffler Architect and ZAS (Zawadzki Armin Stevens) Architects | structural_engineer = Carruthers & Wallace Ltd. | services_engineer = | civil_engineer = | other_designers = Acoustical Engineers - Artec Consultants Inc. | quantity_surveyor = | awards = | designations = | ren_architect = | ren_firm = | ren_str_engineer = | ren_serv_engineer = | ren_civ_engineer = | ren_oth_designers = | ren_qty_surveyor = | ren_awards = | url = http://www.stockeycentre.com/ | nrhp = | references = }}
The '''Charles W. Stockey Centre for the Performing Arts''' is a performance hall and sports museum in [[Parry Sound, Ontario|Parry Sound]], [[Ontario]], Canada. It is the primary performance venue for the annual [[Festival of the Sound]] summer classical music festival. The centre is named for Charles W. Stockey, an early and enthusiastic supporter and board member of the Festival of the Sound.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.stockeycentre.com/charles-w-stockey |title= Charles W. Stockey|publisher= Charles W. Stockey Centre for the Performing Arts|accessdate= 2011-07-04}}</ref> Construction of the CAD$12.4-million centre was started in the spring of 2002 and the official opening took place in {{Start date|2003|July}}.<ref name="History">{{cite web|url= http://www.stockeycentre.com/history |title= History|publisher= Charles W. Stockey Centre for the Performing Arts|accessdate= 2011-07-04}}</ref>
==Facilities== The centre sits on a 1.5-hectare (3.5-acre) site on a [[peninsula]] where the [[Seguin River]] flows into [[Parry Sound]] on [[Georgian Bay]] and adjacent to the town's harbour area. The building has 2,500 square metres (27,000 square feet) of floor space. It includes a 480-seat music hall with acoustics by Artec Consultants<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.artecconsultants.com/03_projects/performing_arts_venues/charles_stockey_centre/festival_performance_hall.html|title= Festival Performance Hall|publisher= Artec Consultants|accessdate= 2011-07-04}}</ref> and the Bobby Orr Hall of Fame, celebrating the Parry Sound native and ice hockey legend [[Bobby Orr]].<ref name="History" /> The centre was designed to look and feel like a Georgian Bay cottage; wood is used extensively for structural and decorative purposes.<ref name="History" />
