{{Unreferenced|date=February 2007}}
'''El Gran Luchadore''' is the name of a masked [[Lucha libre|Mexican professional wrestling]] character in [[World Wrestling Entertainment]], seen on its [[WWE Friday Night SmackDown|SmackDown!]] brand in 2004. El Gran Luchadore (loosely translated from [[Spanish language|Spanish]] to "The Great Fighter/Wrestler," "Luchadore" is also an incorrect spelling, ''luchador'' is the correct spelling) was mainly used as a [[Job (professional wrestling)#Jobbers|jobber]] [[Gimmick (professional wrestling)|gimmick]] to [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Put over|put over]] other wrestlers.

The first WWE wrestler to wrestle as the El Gran Luchadore was [[Paul London]] on April 22, 2004 in a [[Squash (professional wrestling)|squash]] match against [[John Bradshaw Layfield]] (JBL), [[Paul Heyman]] convinced Bradshaw to accept a match with the "Mexican Heavyweight Champion" after hearing that El Gran Luchadore punked out Bradshaw at an airport.

Next up was [[Shannon Moore]] on July 8, 2004, billed as the "champion of [[Mexico]]", would face [[WWE Championship|WWE Champion]] JBL in a ''champion vs. champion match'' (no titles on the line). A second squash match for JBL took an unexpected turn when El Gran Luchadore pulled a switcharoo with [[Eddie Guerrero]] (in El Gran's costume) who came back fighting. When JBL finally clued that it was Guerrero, he ran away from the ring getting counted out in the process, allowing El Gran Luchadore to pick up his first victory.

The next appearance of El Gran Luchadore was on July 15, 2004 edition of ''SmackDown!''. During a Steel Cage match between Guerrero and JBL which saw both men sat on top of the Cage, exchanging punches until El Gran Luchadore ran down and climbed into the cage. This El Gran Luchadore held Eddie Guerrero's leg, allowing Bradshaw to climb down the side of the cage to win. After the match El Gran Luchadore tried to get out of the locked door, but then decided to climb out the way he came in.  Eddie Guerrero got to his feet and climbed up the cage struggling to get him back into the cage. Luchadore was able to get away, but in the struggle Guerrero pulled the mask off of him, revealing him to be the supposedly injured [[Kurt Angle]].

