{{use dmy dates|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Prestonfield | nickname = | image = [[File:Prestonfield.jpg|300px]] | location = [[Linlithgow]], [[West Lothian]] | coordinates = {{coord|55.9727|-3.6121}} | broke_ground = | opened = 1949 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = [[Grass]] | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[Linlithgow Rose F.C.]] (1949–present) | seating_capacity = 2,264 (301 seated) | dimensions = 104 × 65 yards }}
'''Prestonfield''' is a [[association football|football]] stadium in the [[royal burgh]] of [[Linlithgow]], [[West Lothian]], Scotland. It is the home stadium of [[Linlithgow Rose F.C.|Linlithgow Rose]] of the [[East of Scotland Football League]].
The stadium was opened in 1949 and currently consists of a covered and seated stand opposite a covered enclosure with the rest of the ground being concrete terracing. The current capacity is 2,264 of whom 301 can be seated.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.linlithgowrose.co.uk/health--safety|title=Linlithgow Rose - Health and Safety, retrieved August 2018|last=|first=|date=1 August 2018|website=Linlithgow Rose|dead-url=}}</ref>
In July 2018, [[Livingston F.C.]] confirmed that their home ties in the [[2018–19 Scottish League Cup]] Group stage would be held at Prestonfield, due to delays with the installation of a new [[artificial turf]] pitch at their own [[Almondvale Stadium]], situated about {{convert|7|mi|km|0}} from Linlithgow.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44791100|title=Pitch installation delay forces Livingston to move League Cup ties to Prestonfield|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=11 July 2018|accessdate=11 July 2018}}</ref>
