{{Infobox company | name = Ray's Outdoors | logo = | logo_size = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_padding = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-1 code, e.g. "fr" for French. For multiple names in different languages, use {{lang|[code]|[name]}}. --> | former_name = | type = | industry = [[Retail]] | founded = <!-- if known: {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} in [[city]], [[country]] --> | founder = <!-- or: | founders = --> | hq_location = | hq_location_city = | hq_location_country = [[Australia]] | area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = --> | key_people = | products = | brands = | services = | owner = [[Super Retail Group Limited]] | website = [http://www.rays.com.au/ rays.com.au] }}
'''Rays''', formerly called '''Ray's Outdoors''' is an [[Australia|Australian]] [[chain store|chain]] of retail stores with 15 locations across Australia, selling camping, hiking and kayaking equipment and outdoor clothing and footwear. It was founded in 1958 as a single camping store in [[Geelong]]<ref>http://www.superretailgroup.com.au/about-us/our-journey/</ref>. It has been part of [[Super Retail Group]] since 2010<ref>https://www.sbs.com.au/news/refreshed-super-retail-lifts-fy-profit-62</ref><ref>http://www.superretailgroup.com.au/about-us/rays-outdoors/</ref>.
In about April 2018 several Rays began to be liquidated, with the remainder stores planned to be merged with its recently acquired, New Zealand chain [[Macpac]]. <ref>https://www.thecourier.com.au/story/5346516/rays-outdoors-to-close-its-ballarat-store/</ref>
