{{Infobox Sport governing body |assocname= South African Table Tennis Board |abbrev = SATTB |logo= South African Table Tennis Board.jpeg |sport= Table Tennis |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = [[South Africa]] |founded = {{Start date|1948}} |aff = [[International Table Tennis Federation|ITTF]] |affdate = 1950<ref>[https://www.ittf.com/directory/ Directory], ITTF, accessed 21 September 2017.</ref> |region = |regionyear = |headquarters = [[Pretoria]] |location = |president = Yusuf Carrim<ref>[http://www.tabletennis.co.za/index.php/about-us/sattb-board National Executive Members], SATTB, accessed 21 September 2017.</ref> |chairman = |chairperson = |chair = |chiefexec = |secretary = |coach = |womenscoach = |key staff = |operating income = |sponsor = |year closed = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url = www.tabletennis.co.za |countryflag= South Africa |countryflag2= |countryflag3= }}
The '''South African Table Tennis Board''' ('''SATTB''') is the national governing body responsible for [[table tennis]] in [[South Africa]]. The organisation has been affiliated to both the [[International Table Tennis Federation|ITTF (International Table Tennis Federation)]] since 1950, and the [[African Table Tennis Federation]]. SATTB is based in Pretoria.
==History== The unification between the then South African Table Tennis Union (SATTU) founded in 1939 and the South African Table Tennis Board (SATTB) established in 1948 occurred in 1991.<ref>[http://www.tabletennis.co.za/index.php/about-us/our-history Our History], SATTB, accessed 21 September 2017.</ref> SATTU got affiliated to South African National Olympic Committee (SANOC) and the Confederation of South African Sports (COSAS), while SATTB got affiliated to the [[International Table Tennis Federation]] (ITTF), [[African Table Tennis Federation]] (ATTF), and National Olympic Sports Congress (NOSC). SATTB was a member of both the ITTF and ATTF during the apartheid-era period of isolation.
Subsequent to unification, South Africa received two wild cards to the [[South Africa at the 1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Summer Olympics]] with Louis Boha (SATTU) and Cheryl Roberts (SATTB) as representatives.<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/RSA/summer/1992/TTN/ South Africa Table Tennis at the 1992 Barcelona Summer Games], Sports Reference, accessed 21 September 2017.</ref> SATTB is registered with [[SASCOC]] as the officially recognised governing body.<ref>[http://www.sascoc.co.za/2014/01/21/table-tennis-board-of-southern-africa South African Table Tennis Board], [[SASCOC]], accessed 21 September 2017.</ref>
