{{Infobox stadium | name = Stade Jean Alric | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Stade Jean-Alric, tribune honneur.jpg | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = | coordinates = {{coord|44|55|28|N|2|25|46|E|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1924 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = grass | main_contractors = | capacity = 9,000 | suites = | tenants = [[Stade Aurillacois Cantal Auvergne]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
'''Stade Jean Alric''' is a [[rugby union]] [[stadium]], in [[Aurillac]], [[France]].
It is the home stadium of [[Stade Aurillacois Cantal Auvergne]]. The stadium can hold 9,000 people (7,000 seated).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldstadiums.com/europe/countries/france/auvergne.shtml |title=Stadiums in France Auvergne|publisher=Worldstadiums.com|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref>
It has been named after [[Jean Alric]], a player of the club shot by the [[SS]] on June 5, 1944.
